summary: This event discusses Hydrogen Embrittlement (HE) in metals, focusing on the diffusion and trapping of hydrogen atoms in high-strength metallic materials. It highlights the critical issues faced in industries like aerospace and energy due to HE, and presents theoretical models that predict HE under various conditions, offering insights into mechanisms such as hydrogen-enhanced localized plasticity and hydrogen-induced decohesion.
title: Theoretical Approaches to Hydrogen Diffusion and Embrittlement in Metals
